HEADWORD: Tubulibranchiata
<hw>Tu`bu*li*bran`chi*a"ta</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos>
<ety>[NL., from L. <ets>tubulus</ets> a little tube +
<ets>branchia</ets> a gill.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A group of
gastropod mollusks having a tubular shell. Vermetus is an
example.</def>⟦br⟧
